TY  - JOUR
T1  - Communication Patterns as Determinants of Organizational Identification in a Virtual Organization
AU  - Wiesenfeld, Batia M.
AU  - Raghuram, Sumita
AU  - Garud, Raghu
Y1  - 1999/12/01
PY  - 1999
DA  - 1999/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/orsc.10.6.777
DO  - 10.1287/orsc.10.6.777
T2  - Organization Science
JF  - Organization Science
JO  - Organization Science
SP  - 777
EP  - 790
VL  - 10
IS  - 6
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Recent advances in information technologies provide employees the freedom to work from any place and at any time. Such temporal and spatial dispersion, however, weakens the ties that bind organizations and their members. We suggest that organizational identification may be the critical glue linking virtual workers and their organizations. We explore the role that information technologies play in the creation and maintenance of a common identity among decoupled organization members.
